description:
Everyone is tired of paying for subscriptions. The subscription economy locks us into price hikes, closed ecosystems, and endless monthly fees, where we own nothing but pay forever.

#subscriptions #techreaction #ownnothingpayforever #techanalysis #primesubscription

I am creating these videos for entertainment and educational purposes. Please do not contact or harass any individuals featured in the clips. These clips are included to critique broader trends in the tech industry, particularly where innovation is used to justify exploitative or user-unfriendly practices. I do not condone online bullying or harassment in any form. 

If you enjoyed this content, please consider subscribing to the channel!

All thoughts and opinions are my own.

00:00 Intro
00:20 Printer Subscription

15:36 Disney Subscription

The reason companies get away with doing these things is simple:  we let them.   It's not capitalism's fault - in fact, the principals of capitalism are the cure.  If you don't buy it because it's badly designed, cumbersome, etc., then they don't make money, and they'll have to change it.   But we have a lot of idiots these days who just do the dumb thing and keep paying for bad products.  I think they're the same idiots who kept spam email profitable for so long.

Also, it's not capitalism that "requires that companies keep growing profits".  It's the corporate/Wall St system that pushes companies to constantly increase value for shareholders.   Small businesses don't have that problem.
